      • invoke

        protected void invoke(ExecutionContext context,
                      ArgumentIterator args)
               throws ResolvedControlThrowable
        Description copied from class: AbstractLibFunction
        Invokes the function in the context context with arguments passed in the iterator args.

        This is the method that is meant to be implemented by the function implementation. The function should not retain a reference to context or args beyond the scope of its invocation. In particular, context and args should not be part of suspended state if this method throws a control throwable.

        context and args are guaranteed to be non-null when the function is invoked via Dispatch.

        Specified by:
        invoke in class AbstractLibFunction
        Parameters:
        context - execution context, must not be null
        args - call arguments, must not be null
        Throws:
        ResolvedControlThrowable - if the call initiates a non-local control change
